Disability
Under the Equality Act 2010, a person is considered to have a disability 'if they have a physical or mental impairment, and the impairment has a substantial and long-term adverse effect on his or her ability to carry out normal day-to-day activities'. Please be advised any information provided will be confidential and will not be disclosed to recruiting manager or interview panel.

Please indicate below if you consider yourself to have such a disability.

*If you would like to note more than one disability, please select "Two or More impairments and/or disabling medical conditions" and input any details you wish to divulge in the description box.

