Disability Confident
The University is a Disability Confident employer and welcomes interest from disabled applicants. Under our Interview Guarantee Scheme we guarantee an interview to disabled applicants meeting all the essential criteria of a role.

https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/disability-confident-campaign

Do you wish to be considered under the Disability Confident scheme?


Criminal Convictions
Applicants for all posts at the University are required to disclose previous unspent convictions. If you are applying for an 'excluded' post, you are required to disclose all previous convictions, whether spent or unspent (other than protected cautions or protected convictions which do not need to be disclosed).

For further information please visit https://www.gov.uk/tell-employer-or-college-about-criminal-record/check-your-conviction-caution

Do you have any previous criminal convictions?

