British Armed Forces Veterans
As part of Canterbury Christ Church University's commitment to the British Armed Forces Covenant and to ensure that ex-armed forces personnel are not disadvantaged as a result of their service, veterans applying for a job at the University will be guaranteed the offer of an interview provided that they meet the essential criteria for the advertised role and are able to answer one of the questions below.

Do you consider yourself to be a veteran of the British Armed Forces (BAF)?

Are you currently serving in the BAF and within 12 weeks of discharge date?

Were you in long-term employment in the BAF within the last 5 years?


Care Leaver Covenant
As an Equal Opportunities employer, the University has made a commitment to the Government initiated Care Leaver Covenant, and we aim to ensure a 'Robust Employment Offer' to Care Experienced young people aged between 16-25 in their transition from care to independence. We support the access of meaningful opportunities by ensuring that candidates applying for a job at the University will be guaranteed an offer of an interview provided that they meet the essential criteria for the advertised role and are able to tick the option below.

About the CLC: https://mycovenant.org.uk/opportunities/canterbury-christ-church-university/

Were you under the care of a Local Authority before the age of 18?


